"n.抒情短诗，情歌，合唱曲 【记】 西班牙首都马德里(Ma drid)+gal n. 抒情短诗; 中世纪抒情牧歌 【记】源于西班牙首都马德里(Madrid)流行的抒情短诗人. 【记】音：马德里歌，马德里的歌，情歌，马德里是西班牙首都，盛产情歌歌手，如情歌王子胡里奥.伊格莱西亚斯之类的 madrigal (n.)  ""short love poem,"" also ""part-song for three or more voices,"" 1580s, from Italian madrigale, probably from Venetian dialect madregal ""simple, ingenuous,"" from Late Latin matricalis ""invented, original,"" literally ""of or from the womb,"" from matrix (genitive matricis) ""womb"" (see matrix)."
